<h2>REST IRacing Data</h2>

<h3><a target="new-window" href='https://www.data-iracing.net/hal/browser.html#'/>https://www.data-iracing.net</a></h3>

<p>&nbsp;<p>
<h4>Details</h4>
<p>This service provides a full REST compliant set of resources
   detailing drivers, races, leagues and other
   associated data from the iracing platform.
   (<a href="http://www.iracing.com">http://www.iracing.com</a>).</p>

<p>This data is extracted on a regular basis from iracing's site, and
   provided at <a target="new-window" href='https://www.data-iracing.net/hal/browser.html#'/>https://www.data-iracing.net</a>
  as set of highly structured RESTful resources.</p>

<p>For a reference codebase to demonstrate access to this data service, see the web-widgets open source project
   at  <a target="new-window" href="https://github.com/vipoo/iracing-widgets">https://github.com/vipoo/iracing-widgets</a>

<h4>Resources</h4>

<p>The resoources of the service are returned in <a target="new-window" href="http://stateless.co/hal_specification.html">JSON+HAL format</a>.</p>

<p>Each resource contains a set of links to other associated resources, thus allow easy
   discovery of the data available.  The root resource provides entries links to all resources available.<p>

<p>The service is hosted using a self-signed certificate (so you will get warnings if you
   attempt to view the resources through your browser).  You will need to authorise your
   browser to accept my certificate.</p>

<p>The resources returned, will contain:</p>
<ul>
  <li>A set of key attributes relevant to the resouce (eg: name for the driver's name)</li>
  <li>A <b>_links</b> attribute, detailing a set of links to access associated resources</li>
  <li>An optional <b>_embedded</b> attribute, containing other associated resources</li>
  <li>An optional <b>_meta</b> attribute, detailing aspects of the resource object - eg: time resources was retrieved from iracing.com</li>
</ul>

<p>For example, the resource at <a target="new-window" href="https://www.data-iracing.net/hal/browser.html#/drivers/82503/details/road">/drivers/82503/details/road</a>
