<h4>Accessing the data</h4>

<p>This data is provided as is, with no warranties, etc, for your use in your web site and application.</p>

<h4>Authorisation</h4>

<p>Access to the service, at the moment, requires no authorisation.  A warning is returned in each resource
if you access without an authorization token.

<p>The open access is for a limited time only, and access tokens will soon be needed to access this service.
The service will accept a valid iracing member's username/password for access.  Or you can request an access
token now, by sending a PM to me (Dean Netherton), within the iRacing forums.
<a target="new-window" href="https://members.iracing.com">members.iracing.com</a></p>

<p>To supply your access/token, you need to supply a Basic Auth header entry in your request, with your
   credentials encoded (not encypted) in base64.  You can use the <a target="new-window" href="https://www.base64decode.org/">this site</a> to encode your details.</p>

<p>For example, if your username is 'Aladdin' and your password is: 'open sesame' then the header would be:
<pre>Authorization: Basic QWxhZGRpbjpvcGVuIHNlc2FtZQ==</pre>

<p>See <a target="new-window" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basic_access_authentication
">wikipedia</a> and google on how to supply Authorization header. (As the traffic to the service
is encypted, your password can not be seen by others.)</p>

